{title: Old Faithful (Horse's Prayer)}
{artist: Eddy Arnold}
{composer: Written by Michael Carr and Jimmy Kennedy}

[C]Old faithful we [F]rode the range [C]together
Old faithful in every kind of [G7]weather
When your [C]roundup days are [C7]over
There'll be [F]pastures white with [C]clover
For you old [G7]faithful pal of [C]mine
Hurry up old fellow cause the moon is yellow tonight
Hurry up old fellow cause the moon is mellow and [G7]bright
There's a [C]coyote howling to the moon [C7]above
So [F]carry me back to the [C]one I love
Hurry up old fellow cause we [G7]gotta get home [C]tonight
Repeat #1
For you old [G7]faithful pal of [C]mine